Topics:
1. Wisdom in the head, reins in the hand (Estonian proverb)
2. Holidays and anniversaries
3. Running errands in town
4. Friendship is worth more than moneyObjectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of this course is to enhance students Estonian language skills from Waystage level to the Thershold level. During the course the students will develop their oral communication skills, learn relevant vocabulary, practice informal conversation and carry out procedures/information excange needed for getting services. This will be done through a variety of tasks, mainly developing the following two language skills: Speaking: asking for information and explanation, expressing one's opinion (agreeing/disagreeing), making suggestions, describing events and phnomena, comparing and carrying out simple analysis. Listening: practicing understanding of what is heard on everyday topics, finding information in recorded texts on familiar subjects, following simple news on the radio and on TV, practicing everyday telephone conversationsLearning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course the students will be able to
- hold a conversation on everyday topics without preparation;
- use simple language structures to describe their studies, experience and life;
- explain/justify their points of view;
- talk about what they have heard or seen if the subject is familiar to them;
- get the gist of recorded audio materials that are of interest to them;
- undestand simple conversations by native speakers
- understand the main idea of radio and TV broadcasts that are on everyday topics.
